Arizona prohibits a person from knowingly possessing a firearm if the person:

Arizona also prohibits any person who was previously adjudicated delinquent for an offense that would be a felony if committed by an adult, from possessing, using or carrying a firearm within ten years from the date of his or her adjudication or release or escape from custody if the person was previously adjudicated for an offense that, if committed as an adult, would constitute:

postcontent: This is the renowned and very limited Wilson Combat Patriot Elite 5” .45acp. This pistol was designed by Trey Tenery, Victory Gun & Guitar Works, in Dallas, Texas and is only available at this location. The pistol starts out as a hand selected carbon steel frame and slide. The frame and V-grip are then carefully fitted to the slide and then sent off the Turnbull Restorations for color case hardening treatment. The slide and small parts are meticulously prepared for the high polish blued finish. The small parts, pins, and screws are all even further exhibition polished. The pistol features a flush cut bull barrel with steep reverse crown and a fitted flush plug. The V-grip is a modern upgrade to the “A1” rounded backstrap of the grip. It fills the palm of the hand and increases the contact surface area of grip. The slide stop pin is recessed with bevel in the frame. The front strap has a unique checkering pattern designed by Vic Tibbets, the custom shop manager for Wilson Combat. This design gives plenty of grip, while allowing for the beautiful case hardening to been seek on the frontstrap next to the grips. The front sight is a high visibility gold bead with U notch serrated rear battle sight. The pistol comes in the logo Wilson Combat bag with two factory magazines.

title: For Sale:  Russian SKS - 1954 Tula, Numbers Match, Excellent!
postcontent: Offered here is a very nice Russian SKS that was built at the Tula Arsenal in 1954, rearsenaled in Russia at a later date, and imported by KBI. The rifle was represented to me as ‘unfired’ when I bought it from a local collector, but all armory-refurbished rifles were undoubtedly fired at some point. That said, the bolt face, barrel, crown, bayonet, etc. are all in great condition with no obvious evidence that this rifle has been shot. The previous owner removed the Russian armory cosmoline (thankfully). I have not shot this SKS, but everything appears to operate correctly, and I am confident that it will function perfectly whenever the next owner shoots it. The 1954 Tula’s have a chrome-lined barrel, and these Russian SKS are essentially the gold standard. The rifle comes with the full KBI retail package, including an ammo pouch, stripper clips, oil bottle and storage pouch, butt-plate tool kit, rifle sling, and manual. Stamped numbers match throughout, although the Arctic Birch (Russian Birch) rifle stock has the original serial number ‘X’ed through and a re-arsenal ‘box-and-slash’ stamp is visible. I installed a dark earth Tapco ‘tactical’ stock on this SKS a few months ago when I planned to keep and shoot it, but I recently got another 7.62x39 rifle, so this fine SKS package needs a new home. Upon request, I will provide the original package for the Tapco stock in case the new owner wants to remove and store the ‘tactical’ stock and re-install the original Russian wood stock. Please inspect the photos carefully, they are an essential part of the description for this very nice Tula Arsenal SKS. I will answer questions promptly and/or supply additional photos of any part or angle of interest, but please ask only if you are serious about the firearm.

title: For Sale:  Ruger Police Service Six .357 Magnum
postcontent:
For sale is my Ruger Police Service Six .357 Magnum. 

Serial number places its manufacture in 1985, I believe. I think the Security Six family of revolvers were manufactured from the early '70s till about 1988. 

This is a 4" barrel, six shot, stainless .357 Magnum. It has fixed sights: front ramp and rear frame channel. 

It comes with 5 pairs of grips as seen in the picture. Pachmayr, Hogue, large wooden, and two small pairs of wooden (don't know why previous owner had 2 pairs of the small wooden). In any event, you are set on grips, I should say. 

Also comes with original box, 2 speed loaders, a dual speed loader pouch for a duty belt, and 2 boxes of ammo: Hornady 125gr FTX hollow points (25 rds) and Fiocchi 142gr range ammo (50 rds). No picture on the speed loaders and pouch, sorry. 

It is ridiculous how easy this gun disassembles. You take off the grips, then the main trigger spring pops out, then the hammer, then the main trigger assembly comes off the frame. I watched one YouTube video and took this thing apart in 90 seconds for cleaning. 

I would say this is a 90-95% gun. Very clean, metal looks great. Trigger is smooth in double action and super sweet single action - light crisp break at about 3.5 lbs. Cylinder lockup is tight and rifling and crown look great. 

In the market for a 4" stainless, .357 Magnum beauty? This is a solid Ruger, capable of firing the hottest .357 full-house ammo without worrying. Built like a tank. 

Asking $490. Will not ship. Cash only. Will only drive to meet if a reasonable distance. 

Please call or text  REDACTED
